<div class="p-6 dark:bg-gray-900 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200  space-y-6">
  <div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">1. Setup for JavaScript Projects</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
      <li><strong>Install VSCode</strong>: <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/" class="text-blue-600 underline">https://code.visualstudio.com/</a></li>
      <li><strong>Enable Autosave</strong>: <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">File &gt; Auto Save</code> or use <code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">Ctrl+Shift+P</code> → type “Auto Save”</li>
      <li><strong>Install Node.js</strong>: VSCode relies on it for running JavaScript backend and tools – <a href="https://nodejs.org/" class="text-blue-600 underline">https://nodejs.org/</a></li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <hr class="border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-700">

  <div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">2. Essential Extensions</h3>
    <p class="mb-2">Search in Extensions (<code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">Ctrl+Shift+X</code>):</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
      <li> <strong>ESLint</strong> — Lints your JavaScript code (auto-fix issues)</li>
      <li> <strong>Prettier - Code Formatter</strong> — Auto-formats code</li>
      <li> <strong>Live Server</strong> — For real-time reloading in the browser</li>
      <li> <strong>JavaScript (ES6) code snippets</strong> — Faster coding</li>
      <li> <strong>Path Intellisense</strong> — Auto-completes file paths</li>
      <li> <strong>GitLens</strong> — Git made powerful inside VSCode</li>
      <li> <strong>Thunder Client</strong> — Like Postman, for testing APIs</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <hr class="border-gray-300 dark:border-gray-700">

  <div>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">3. Keyboard Shortcuts (Speed!)</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
      <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">Ctrl+P</code> → Quick file navigation</li>
      <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">Ctrl+Shift+P</code> → Command palette</li>
      <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">Alt+↑/↓</code> → Move line up/down</li>
      <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">Ctrl+/</code> → Toggle comment</li>
      <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">Ctrl+B</code> → Toggle sidebar</li>
      <li><code class="bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-1 rounded">Ctrl+~</code> → Toggle terminal</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
